tspan.tspan: When IOS learns about an IP prefix from several routing information sources,
it selects the best source, by comparing the Admisitrative Distance of each
source. The source with the lowest Administrative Distance is the best.
Between a source's routes, IOS uses the source's metric to select the
best route. Typically, the route with the lowest metric is the best route.
Metrics between routing information sources are not comparable.

text.tspan: only the best route gets into the Routing table
